================================================================================
DATA SOURCES AND ATTRIBUTIONS
================================================================================

This repository includes data derived from the following sources:

1. Menota Corpus
   Old Icelandic texts from the Medieval Nordic Text Archive (Menota);
   texts and their annotated entites were extractred from Menotic XML, processed, and converted, to CoNLL format. 
   License: CC BY-SA 4.0
   Source: https://menota.org

   Citation:
   @misc{menota,
     author = {Medieval Nordic Text Archive},
     title = {Welcome page for Menota},
     url = {https://www.menota.org/EN_forside.xhtml}
   }

2. Icelandic Parsed Historical Corpus (IcePaHC)
   Used to augment the existing Menota training data above, data extracted from the PoS-tagged texts. 
   License: CC BY 4.0
   Source: https://repository.clarin.is/repository/xmlui/handle/20.500.12537/325

   Citation:
   @misc{20.500.12537/325,
     title = {Icelandic Parsed Historical Corpus (IcePaHC) 2024.03},
     author = {Wallenberg, Joel C. and Ingason, Anton Karl and
               Sigurðsson, Einar Freyr and Rögnvaldsson, Eiríkur},
     url = {http://hdl.handle.net/20.500.12537/325},
     note = {CLARIN-IS},
     copyright = {Creative Commons - Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)},
     year = {2024}
   }

3. IceBERT (Pre-trained Language Model)
   Base model used for transfer learning; base model used for normalised NER model, finetuned for diplomatic NER model. 
   License: CC BY 4.0
   Source: https://huggingface.co/vesteinn/IceBERT

   Citation:
   @inproceedings{snaebjarnarson-etal-2022-warm,
     title = "A Warm Start and a Clean Crawled Corpus - A Recipe for Good Language Models",
     author = "Snæbjarnarson, Vésteinn and Símonarson, Haukur Barri and
               Ragnarsson, Pétur Orri and Ingólfsdóttir, Svanhvít Lilja and
               Jónsson, Haukur and Thorsteinsson, Vilhjalmur and Einarsson, Hafsteinn",
     booktitle = "Proceedings of the Thirteenth Language Resources and Evaluation Conference",
     month = jun,
     year = "2022",
     address = "Marseille, France",
     publisher = "European Language Resources Association",
     url = "https://aclanthology.org/2022.lrec-1.464",
     pages = "4356--4366"
   }

================================================================================
MIM-GOLD-NER (NOT INCLUDED IN THIS REPOSITORY)
================================================================================

Some experiments in this repository use MIM-GOLD-NER (Modern Icelandic NER dataset) for training data augmentation.

License: Custom restrictive license (non-redistributable)
Source: https://repository.clarin.is/repository/xmlui/handle/20.500.12537/140

IMPORTANT: MIM-GOLD-NER is NOT included in this repository due to license
restrictions. Users must obtain it separately from CLARIN.IS and agree to
their license terms. See MIM_GOLD_NER_INSTRUCTIONS.md for setup instructions.

Citation:
@misc{20.500.12537/140,
  title = {MIM-GOLD-NER – named entity recognition corpus (21.09)},
  author = {Ingólfsdóttir, Svanhvít Lilja and Guðjónsson, Ásmundur Alma
            and Loftsson, Hrafn},
  url = {http://hdl.handle.net/20.500.12537/140},
  note = {CLARIN-IS},
  copyright = {Icelandic Mim Gold Standard for Named Entity Recognition (NER)},
  year = {2020}
}

The following experiment directories contain only README files (no data):
- data/normalised/normalised_ner_data/norm_menota_ihpc_mim/
- data/normalised/normalised_ner_data/norm_menota_ihpc_resamp_mim/
- data/diplomatic/diplomatic_ner_data/dipl_menota_mim/
- data/diplomatic/diplomatic_ner_data/dipl_menota_ihpc_mim/
- data/diplomatic/diplomatic_ner_data/dipl_menota_resamp_mim/
- data/diplomatic/diplomatic_ner_data/dipl_menota_ihpc_resamp_mim/

Users who obtain MIM-GOLD-NER can use the provided scripts to generate these
experiment datasets locally.

